SLUG: ks-global-estates

# Startup Brief — KS Global Estates

## Project
Premium marketing + property-discovery website for KS Global Estates, a global
real estate firm. They want a visually striking, user-friendly site that
communicates their brand and services and showcases listings. Michael's framing:
a full frontend + backend property app with a mock DB of real estate listings
browsable as a LIST and on a MAP (same map tech as the MN State Park Tracker:
Leaflet + OpenStreetMap tiles). It must read as human-crafted, deliberately NOT
"AI-built." Target feature richness: 10/10 — a genuinely full-featured,
production-quality demo with several real working features.

## Recommended demo direction (high level; planner to refine)
Build a bespoke luxury-real-estate web app: a branded landing/brand section plus
a full property-discovery experience. Single most impressive thing: a
synchronized split view where an interactive Leaflet map (custom price-pin
markers, hover/click sync, cluster or fly-to) sits beside a live, filterable
listings grid — filtering, sorting, and searching update BOTH the list and the
map in real time, and clicking a pin opens a rich property detail view. Back it
with a mock property DB (20–30+ listings: houses, condos, estates, penthouses,
global cities) driving list/map/detail. Scale to 10/10 with real working
features: full-text + faceted filters (price, beds/baths, property type,
city/country, sqft, status), sort, map<->list sync, saved/favorites (persisted),
detail pages with image galleries, an inquiry/contact flow, and a polished
responsive luxury layout. Property IMAGERY ONLY — houses, condos, estates,
interiors, skylines — never unrelated stock. Backend as a Flask blueprint or
realistic mock data (this environment cannot use the Surface runner); point the
demo at a mock/local source with an api.michaelwegter.com base for the deployed
build.

## Anti-AI-tells guidance (explicit client requirement — respect it)
Researcher must gather concrete tell-tale signs of AI-generated sites and the
planner/demo-builder must EXCLUDE them. Known offenders to avoid: generic
centered hero + three-icon feature row, purple/indigo gradient blobs, "Lorem"
vibes and empty filler copy, cookie-cutter Inter-everywhere type, identical
rounded cards in a rigid 3-col grid, fake logo strips, emoji bullets, symmetric
"AI slop" spacing. Counter with a bespoke luxury design system: distinctive
editorial typography, asymmetric/edvertorial layouts, real property content,
intentional whitespace, refined motion, a specific brand palette. Design must NOT
resemble michaelwegter.com's look; it must fit high-end global real estate.

## Constraints / risks / red flags
- U.S.-only applicants — Michael qualifies; the cover letter should read as a
  U.S.-based developer. No blocker.
- Vague brief (no explicit budget/timeline/pages). Intake must still extract
  every stated requirement; treat "professional, visually appealing,
  user-friendly, strong portfolio, high quality, reasonable timeframe/budget,
  frontend+backend, mock property DB, list + map, property imagery only, not
  AI-looking, 10/10 richness" as the concrete requirement set.
- Environment: live site/API/Surface unreachable here — verify the demo LOCALLY
  (build + localhost Playwright/QA) and deploy blind via git push.
- No real brand assets known yet — researcher confirms whether KS Global Estates
  has an existing site/logo/colors; if none, planner invents a credible bespoke
  luxury identity and says so.
- Map: reuse the proven Leaflet + OpenStreetMap approach from
  mn-state-park-tracker (no Mapbox token dependency). Ensure map tiles/markers
  load with no console errors on first paint.

## Quality + naming guidance for downstream
- intake: extract every explicit requirement precisely and near-verbatim into
  brief.json (see requirement set above); flag the anti-AI and property-imagery
  constraints as hard acceptance criteria.
- demo-builder: use slug `ks-global-estates` for the demo folder
  (../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/ks-global-estates/) and the workSamples.js
  entry. Property images ONLY. Include Leaflet + list/map sync as the hero.
- researcher: pull real luxury-real-estate visual conventions + AI-tell
  checklist; source property-only imagery (free stock: houses/condos/estates).
- planner: define a bespoke luxury palette (hex), editorial font pairing (Google
  Fonts), and asymmetric layout that deliberately avoids AI tells.

## handoff
- Produced: startup brief at orchestrator.out; slug locked to `ks-global-estates`
  (matches run folder + demo folder + workSamples entry).
- Decision: hero = synchronized Leaflet map <-> filterable listings grid over a
  20–30 mock-property DB; 10/10 feature scope; bespoke luxury design, property
